      "writtenOn": "2026-03-09T18:54:06Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I like this concept overall, but could we make this API not require a base?\n\n\nFor example:\nsdbusplus::message::object_path(\"/xyz/openbmc_project\", \"inventory\");\n\nis harder to understand as an API than\n\nsdbusplus::message::object_path(\"xyz\", \"openbmc_project\", \"inventory\");\n\nThe prior API could potentially be used unsafely.\n\nsdbusplus::message::object_path(\"//bad_path\", \"inventory\");\n\nAnd still result in a crash, where the later API can\u0027t.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 99,
        "startChar": 0,
        "endLine": 99,
        "endChar": 64
      },
      "revId": "a84a0c502fee45582e1fa0cb0b1a968f2d907702",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": true,
      "key": {
        "uuid": "5c1ca1f3_1e95318f",
        "filename": "include/sdbusplus/message/native_types.hpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
